context:
KR:
&lt;이루고 싶은 것이 없어도 돼.&gt;
EN:
&lt;You don't have to want to achieve anything.&gt;

KR:
&lt;하지만 네가 이 버스에 타고 있는 이상… 좋은 일과 괴로운 일들은 계속 있을 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;But as long as you're on this bus with the rest of us, things will keep happening, both good and bad.&gt;

KR:
&lt;히스클리프는 또 어느새 불같이 화를 낼 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Something's probably going to blow Heathcliff's fuse again.&gt;

KR:
&lt;수감자들이, 동료들이 원치 않게 죽는 모습을 보게 될 거고.&gt;
EN:
&lt;You'll see the Sinners, your friends, get killed again.&gt;

KR:
&lt;비참하게 실패해, 아무것도 이루지 못하는 날을 맞이하기도 할 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;We'll fail again, too. The kind of failure that leaves us with nothing. The kind of failure that leaves us stagnant.&gt;

KR:
&lt;그래도…&gt;
EN:
&lt;But...&gt;

KR:
&lt;그 일들 사이 사이에는 반드시 이런 일들도 있어.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Among those inevitabilities, think about the other things that are sure to happen.&gt;

KR:
돈키호테의 모험담이 시작되면 못 말린다는 듯 끼어들어 주거니 받거니 하게 될 거야.&gt;
EN:
And when Don Quixote starts to regale us with yet another one of her tales of adventure, you're going to join in to indulge her.&gt;

KR:
&lt;좋아하는 음식을 먹고, 로쟈가 맛에 대해 찬미하는 걸 보며 웃을 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;You know for sure that you'll be listening to Rodya heap praises about her favorite food whenever we get the chance to try them.&gt;

KR:
&lt;버스 창가에 비친 풍경이 문득 새로워져서, 아름답다고 느낄 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;You're going to suddenly realize that the scenery past the bus windows have changed, and that they've become beautiful for once.&gt;

KR:
&lt;뒷자리에서 들려오는 수감자들의 웃음에 이유 없이 행복해질 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;You're going to feel your heart swell for no reason, when you listen to the Sinners laugh and giggle behind you.&gt;

KR:
&lt;왜냐면 말이야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;You know how I know this?&gt;

KR:
&lt;내가 그러고 있거든.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Because I'm talking about myself here.&gt;

KR:
&lt;기억이 없어져서 텅 비어 버린 나를, 이런 나날 나날들로 채워가.&gt;
EN:
&lt;These moments in time… they’re what I use to fill the void my memories left behind.&gt;

KR:
&lt;끝이라고 생각하고 밟았던 마지막 지점은…&gt;
EN:
&lt;One end... or, at least what we thought would be the end...&gt;

KR:
&lt;항상 다음 출발선이었어.&gt;
EN:
&lt;... was always just the starting line for something new.&gt;

KR:
&lt;항상 끝을 밟아왔다고 생각했지만, 우리는 앞으로 나아가고 있었던 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Each finish line was just another arbitrary mark, another step in our journey, right?&gt;

KR:
&lt;그 작은 발걸음들이 모이고 모여서… 살아가게 해줬어.&gt;
EN:
&lt;And it's those little steps that... keep us going.&gt;

KR:
&lt;그리고 홍루 너 또한… 그렇게 되어가고 있어.&gt;
EN:
&lt;And hey, Hong Lu... you're not stagnating. You're changing, too.&gt;

KR:
&lt;말해봐. 가치우의 작전을, 너는 왜 받아들인 거야?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Tell me. Why did you decide to go with Jia Qiu's plan?&gt;

KR:
&lt;그래, 네 마음도… 그렇게 변해가고 있었던 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Yeah, and that's... how your heart's been changing.&gt;

KR:
&lt;너도 모르는 사이에.&gt;
EN:
&lt;In ways you hadn’t seen.&gt;

KR:
&lt;결국 스스로를 구할 수 있는 건… 너뿐일 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;But at the end of the day... only you can save yourself.&gt;

KR:
&lt;그럼에도 불구하고 네가 바라보는 세상은 항상 아름다울 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;But the world you witness will always be beautiful.&gt;

KR:
&lt;홍루, 너는 누구보다 상냥하니까.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Because you are a kind person, Hong Lu. Kinder than anyone else.&gt;

KR:
&lt;무엇보다 청명한 옥색이겠지.&gt;
EN:
&lt;So, your world must be painted in the fairest color of jade.&gt;

KR:
&lt;네가 모아둔 꽃잎들을 보여주면 되는 거야.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Then, show them the petals you’ve gathered.&gt;
